review:
This game has a beautiful atmosphere, graphics, idea and it's really enjoyable to see all this. But it has a thing that unacceptable for the racing game -- really handling:
  - Car's steering is so slow, its like a grandma trying to park, not a rally;
  - The cars itself feels more like an airplane on each jump. There's more problem with sense of speed and cameras, I think, but about this later;
  - I feel like the car automatically counter steer even with all "driving helpers" disabled;
  - Sometimes you can randomly loose control after jump, even if you jump straight forward on the asphalt. It's really annoying considering that you can't do a fast counter steer;
  - The "counter steering factor" option makes you loose control even on straight road, this was the first thing I've disabled;

And with all this, there's another things that affect gameplay:
  - No sense of speed, so 150km/h feels like 30km/h and at the start you will crash in every tree you see;
  - Camera is to high above the car. You can't see the road with it, so on each hill that you don't know -- you will fly away and most of the turns -- will feel differently because of road incline you don't see.
  - There's no mini map and/or navigator, you will need to remember all the tracks.

Somehow I got used to this handling and even set some good times in time attack mode, but it's annoys me most of the time. I mean, this game still has better handling than all NFS's after 2010. :) But I don't think I'll play it after I get the achievements.

My conclusion is if you prefer atmosphere, if you want some hard arcade racing game that will force you to retry the races, or you don't care about your race results, then you will definitely buy it. But if you want an arcade race to enjoy the driving -- this game is not for you.

This is a review after edit, it was positive, and remains positive. This game is an amazing piece of artwork and is clearly taken care of by Funselektor. It looks great, drives great, sounds great, but there are some things to consider before buying. After having done over 70 hours and over 1000 stages, I can tell a couple of things that were wrong when the game released and are still wrong now: 
- flickering textures and jagged edges, most clear around water area and at night on mountain hills for instance;
- frame drops in some maps with denser surroundings, like forests in Norway or Finland - although these are not as noticeable anymore, they still appear from time to time;
- some terrain designs are just flawed - there's a jump in Norway which just launches you straight up in the air pretty much, I don't think it should be like this;
- probably most importantly and annoyingly, and it took me a long time to figure it out: the cars' center of gravity is too high - I cannot stress enough how many times I rolled in this game, way more than in any rally game I played. This also attributes to some very strange sliding in high speed (150+ km/h).

All in all those are just minor nitpicks, the only thing I wish for is that Funselektor addresses these (especially the physics) in their next game, because they are truly amazing developers.
